<div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
    <!-- Indicators -->
    <ol class="carousel-indicators">
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="2"></li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Wrapper for slides -->
    <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="item active">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkInProgress.jpg" alt="Los Angeles">
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkInProgress.jpg" alt="Chicago">
        </div>

        <div class="item">
            <img src="~/Content/Images/WorkInProgress.jpg" alt="New York">
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Left and right controls -->
    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="prev">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
    </a>
    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" data-slide="next">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
    </a>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>How to Get Started?</h2>
        <p>
            Hello Centric Employees! Let's start complimenting the hard work done by your co-workers! To get started, please register at the top right corner. Once this is done, you will be redirected to a profile creation page. Once this is done, it's time to start recognizing all the hard work done! For any questions that need to be answered, please visit the "FAQ" page.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>What is the Purpose?</h2>
        <p>The purpose of this application is to allow employees to recognize and be recognized based on Centric's Core Values.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Who Created This App?</h2>
        <p>
            This application was created in Athens, Ohio at Ohio University. This was developed by Austin Doyle, Hunter McCollough, Xin Ding, Jeff Reimann, and Adam Pierce as a team for MIS 4200. This class partners with Centric to provide an opportunity to gain experience working with technology and the project management technique Scrum.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
